<item>
            <title>[TIKA-126] Add Parser.parse(InputStream, Metadata) for metadata extraction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-126</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In some cases a client is just interested in the parsed metadata and not the extracted text content. It is easy to ignore the text content by just passing a dummy DefaultHandler to the existing parse() method, but many parsers could avoid a lot of work if they knew in advance that the text content is not needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus I want to add a parse(InputStream, Metadata) signature to the Parser interface. I&apos;ll also add an AbstractParser base class with a trivial implementation of that method:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    public abstract AbstractParser implements Parser {&lt;br/&gt;
        public void parse(InputStream stream, Metadata metadata) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            parse(stream, new DefaultHandler(), metadata);
        }
&lt;p&gt;    }&lt;/p&gt;</description>
